\cf0 The concept of urban gardening has gained immense popularity as cities become denser and green spaces rarer. Enthusiasts and environmentalists alike see it as a solution to many urban challenges. The primary allure is its accessibility; anyone with a balcony, rooftop, or small patch of land can create their own green haven. This trend brings both aesthetic value and practical benefits to neighborhoods that might otherwise lack greenery.\
++----------\
A key factor driving urban gardening is sustainability. By growing even a small portion of one's food, urban dwellers can reduce their reliance on grocery stores and contribute less to the carbon emissions associated with large-scale food production. It also fosters a more direct connection to what we eat, giving city residents a greater appreciation for the work that goes into cultivating vegetables, fruits, and herbs.\
